channel.title: Trouble compiling and changing ip of clients
channel.description:
Whenever I try to compile, I get a "not a specified path" error. I have already changed the 'java' in the batch file to the path towards the jre/jdk thing (sorry, I just really dont get this) and it just doesnt work in general.
When I try to change the IP of the server in the applet_sub-1 or whatever I get this:
Exception in thread "main" java.lang.unsupportedclassversionerror: client : Unsu pported major.minor version 51.0 at java.lang.classloader.defineclass1(native Method) at java.lang.classloader.defineclasscond(unkown source) ... (etc etc about 10 more of these or something similar) Could not find the main class: client. Program will exit. Press any key to continue . . .
so if someone could help me through teamviewer while talking on skype, it would be greatly appreciated ^_^ Pm me your skype I guess if you wanna help
